Meta is competing on its Machine Learning capabilities. The more effective their models are at improving ad performance, the less targeting and personal information matter.

It's a smart strategy, and others are likely to follow.
7/7
#DataScience #MachineLearning

Companies optimize their ads' content based on experimental results. The targeting is behavior-based at the segment, not the individual level. The model acts to obscure personal data by aggregating it into segments.
6/7
#DataScience #MachineLearning

2. Using models to optimize ad effectiveness for a specific segment. Meta and their partners provide access to experimental management systems. Advertisers can test ads to understand their impact on high-value segments.
5/7
#DataScience #MachineLearning

Ads are built to target a segment instead of a person taking the personal data out of the equation and replacing it with customer segment level data. The model does the translation.
4/7
#DataScience #MachineLearning

The models reveal the common traits of each segment and why they are likely to make a purchase. Models also predict the spending per segment so companies can optimize ad performance on their highest value segments.
3/7
#DataScience #MachineLearning

Their behavioral models are optimizing ads without targeting individuals. There are 2 sides to this process.

1. Using models to identify customer segments most likely to buy.
2/7
#DataScience #MachineLearning
